**Issue**
Trying to use any method from `mongoose` into model hook returns unexpected results. Running `Model.remove({ _id: model.id })` returns `{ n:0, ok:1 }` or `Model.findOne({ _id: model.id })` returns `null`. I wanted to confirm my queries were correct so i started strapi with `DEBUG=mquery*` and noticed the same queries are being run when i delete stuff from admin but there it works.

Log from model hook:
`mquery remove project { _id: 5b8d242c8ed455254a124969 } {} +12ms`

Log after deleting from admin:
`mquery remove project { _id: 5b8d242c8ed455254a124969 } {} +2ms`

**Steps to reproduce the problem**
in `afterCreate` hook of any model:
```
// After creating a value.
// Fired after an `insert` query.
afterCreate: async (model) => {
  const res = await Model.remove({ _id: model.id || model._id });
  console.log(res); // { n:0, ok: 1 }
}
```
**What is the expected behavior?**
All methods called from global model should run correctly.
```
// After creating a value.
// Fired after an `insert` query.
afterCreate: async (model) => {
  const res = await Model.remove({ _id: model.id || model._id });
  console.log(res); // { n:1, ok: 1 }
}
```


